12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 401 of Title 51, unless there is
15 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. No elected or appointed public official shall be required to
17 sign any type of nondisclosure agreement with respect to a matter
18 involving the performance of duties by the public official if the
19 nondisclosure agreement relates to a project that would have
20 significant impact on the jurisdiction or jurisdictions in which the
21 project would be located or operate. As used in this subsection,
22 "significant impact" means facilities or operations that would
23 affect electrical power usage, water, or other utility
24 infrastructure and similar factors for at least ten percent (10%) of
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2999 Page 1

1 the residents of the area in which the project or facility is
2 proposed to be located or operated.
3 B. The provisions of this section shall not be applicable to a
4 nondisclosure agreement that a person is requested or required to
5 sign with respect to a matter which is personal or related to
6 litigation or potential litigation which does not involve the
7 performance of any duty imposed directly upon the person because of
8 the appointed or elected office the person occupies.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
10 Passed the House of Representatives the 25th day of March, 2026.
